trialA.output:
# Simple Joke Website

Here's a complete HTML website that displays a random joke from a selection of four when the user clicks a button:

```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Random Joke Generator</title>
    <style>
        body {
            font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
            max-width: 600px;
            margin: 0 auto;
            padding: 20px;
            text-align: center;
            background-color: #f5f5f5;
        }

        h1 {
            color: #333;
            margin-bottom: 20px;
        }

        .container {
            background-color: white;
            border-radius: 10px;
            padding: 20px;
            box-shadow: 0 4px 8px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1);
        }

        #joke-display {
            min-height: 80px;
            margin: 20px 0;
            padding: 15px;
            background-color: #f9f9f9;
            border-radius: 5px;
            font-size: 18px;
            display: flex;
            align-items: center;
            justify-content: center;
        }

        button {
            background-color: #4CAF50;
            color: white;
            border: none;
            padding: 10px 20px;
            font-size: 16px;
            cursor: pointer;
            border-radius: 5px;
            transition: background-color 0.3s;
        }

        button:hover {
            background-color: #45a049;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <div class="container">
        <h1>Random Joke Generator</h1>

        <div id="joke-display">Your joke will appear here...</div>

        <button id="joke-button">Tell me a joke!</button>
    </div>

    <script>
        // Array of jokes
        const jokes = [
            "Why don't scientists trust atoms? Because they make up everything!",
            "I told my wife she was drawing her eyebrows too high. She looked surprised.",
            "What do you call a fake noodle? An impasta!",
            "Why did the scarecrow win an award? Because he was outstanding in his field!"
        ];

        // Get DOM elements
        const jokeDisplay = document.getElementById('joke-display');
        const jokeButton = document.getElementById('joke-button');

        // Add click event listener to the button
        jokeButton.addEventListener('click', function() {
            // Generate random index
            const randomIndex = Math.floor(Math.random() * jokes.length);

            // Display random joke
            jokeDisplay.textContent = jokes[randomIndex];
        });
    </script>
</body>
</html>
```

## How to Use This Website

1. Copy the entire code above
2. Save it as "index.html" on your computer
3. Open the file in any web browser
4. Click the "Tell me a joke!" button to see a random joke from the collection

## Features

- Clean, responsive design that works on mobile and desktop
- Four different jokes that appear randomly when the button is clicked
- Simple animation effect when hovering over the button
- Easy to customize - just add more jokes to the array if desired

You can expand this by adding more jokes to the array or enhancing the design with additional CSS.

