Below is a simple, self-contained HTML file that creates a basic website. When you open it in a web browser and click the button, it will randomly display one of four jokes in a designated area on the page. I've used plain HTML, CSS (for minimal styling), and JavaScript (to handle the randomness and button click).

You can copy-paste this code into a file named `index.html` and open it in any web browser to test it.

```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Random Joke Generator</title>
    <style>
        body {
            font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
            text-align: center;
            margin: 50px;
            background-color: #f0f0f0;
        }
        #joke {
            margin-top: 20px;
            font-size: 18px;
            color: #333;
            border: 1px solid #ccc;
            padding: 15px;
            border-radius: 5px;
            max-width: 600px;
            margin: 20px auto;
        }
        button {
            padding: 10px 20px;
            font-size: 16px;
            cursor: pointer;
            background-color: #007bff;
            color: white;
            border: none;
            border-radius: 5px;
        }
        button:hover {
            background-color: #0056b3;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <h1>Random Joke Generator</h1>
    <p>Click the button to get a random joke!</p>
    <button onclick="tellJoke()">Tell Me a Joke</button>
    <div id="joke">Your joke will appear here...</div>

    <script>
        // Array of four jokes
        const jokes = [
            "Why don't scientists trust atoms? Because they make up everything!",
            "Why did the scarecrow win an award? Because he was outstanding in his field!",
            "What do you call fake spaghetti? An impasta!",
            "Why couldn't the bicycle stand up by itself? It was two-tired!"
        ];

        function tellJoke() {
            // Pick a random index from 0 to 3
            const randomIndex = Math.floor(Math.random() * jokes.length);
            // Display the random joke
            document.getElementById('joke').innerText = jokes[randomIndex];
        }
    </script>
</body>
</html>
```

### How It Works:
- **HTML Structure**: There's a heading, a paragraph, a button, and a `<div>` element to display the joke.
- **CSS Styling**: Basic styles to make it look clean and centered.
- **JavaScript Logic**:
  - An array holds four simple jokes.
  - When the button is clicked, it generates a random number between 0 and 3 (inclusive) using `Math.random()` and `Math.floor()`.
  - It then updates the text in the `<div id="joke">` with the selected joke.

This is a complete, standalone page—no external libraries or servers needed. If you want to add more jokes, modify the styling, or expand it (e.g., with images), let me know!
